In com/badlogic/gdx/scenes/scene2d/ui/Image.java, the function draw() contains the following codes:

```
if (drawable.getClass() == TextureRegionDrawable.class) {
    // codes do the drawing that will consider the rotation
} else
    // codes do the drawing that will NOT consider the rotation
```

This makes SpriteDrawable, the sub-class of TextureRegionDrawable, not be able to rotate in any way. I guess it should be

```
if (drawable instanceof TextureRegionDrawable) {
    // codes do the drawing that will consider the rotation
} else
    // codes do the drawing that will NOT consider the rotation
```

Don't know if there are same mistakes existing in the rest of the source. Please check.
